{
  "texts": [
    "Data streaming is achieved by utilizing existing libraries and tools within the Node.js environment.",
    "Specifically, it creates array buffer binary streams divided into chunks that can be sent to the client-or from the client's local storage to the server-and saved according to the client's requirements.",
    "Moreover, the packages are compressed to ensure secure and efficient streaming.",
    "On the client side, the user can decide whether to retain this information in the local web environment or save it to their storage.",
    "The client-side component was developed using Web sockets via Socket.IO for seamless message passing, connection establishment, and interoperability between the server and client."
  ]
}